## How Long Does SEO Take for Southampton Businesses?

**Months 1–3** — Technical foundations: indexation fixes, Core Web Vitals, structured data, and Google Business Profile optimisation.

**Months 3–6** — Initial ranking improvements as topical authority content indexes. Most clients see measurable traffic increases for mid-competition queries in this window.

**Months 6–12** — Compound growth as authority builds. Competitive Southampton queries in professional services, healthcare, and e-commerce begin yielding page-one positions.

## How Much Does an SEO Consultant in Southampton Cost?

**Technical audits** — £500–£1,200 depending on site size and scope.

**Topical maps** — from £800 to £2,500+ depending on industry complexity.

**Monthly retainers** — from £1,500. Compared to a Southampton SEO agency, independent consultant pricing typically delivers the same senior-level quality at 40–60% of the cost. Initial consultations are free.

